HEADWORD: Nectocalyx
<hw>Nec`to*ca"lyx</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Nectocalyces</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>nhkto`s</grk> swimming + <?/ a calyx.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The swimming bell or umbrella of a
jellyfish of medusa.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the zooids of
certain <ord>Siphonophora</ord>, having somewhat the form, and the
essential structure, of the bell of a jellyfish, and acting as a
swimming organ.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

